               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200517-129-person1265">
                  JOHN 
                  PARTERIDGE
               <interp inst="t18200517-129-person1265" type="surname" value="PARTERIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200517-129-person1265" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200517-129-person1265" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer of Whitechapel. On Saturday morning I stopped Johnson in a passage by Whitechapel Church with the saddle and part of the harness on his back. He said they were his master's, a Mr. Goodwin, of Whitechapel-market. I went to his lodgings, and found Smith in bed there - they lived together. I found the bridle and two whips by the bed-side. He said he knew nothing of them. I found about twenty pick-lock keys concealed in the chimney, with files for making them.</p>
               <p>
            
